I was in this changing room & turned to see my reflection at this angle. I audibly, sarcastically said, ‘oh god that’s attractive!’ then immediately checked myself. I stared a little longer & saw myself through kinder eyes, through the eyes of someone that loves me. 

Would I ever think negatively about anyone else who’s body looked like this? Of course not. So why was my instinct to be hard on myself? Of course the answer to this is super complex but in order to grow we have to unlearn negative self talk. My back rolls & my chubby arms are kinda cute tho aren’t they 🥹 

Your reminder to see yourself through kinder eyes today. Your body is beautiful, & also the least interesting thing about you. Love you 💖

It’s @sarahowensmusic birthday so let me tell you about her 💖👇🏼

5 years ago I was on a weekend visit to Edinburgh, in a club toilet, & Sarah tapped me on the shoulder & told me she liked my shirt 😅 LONG story short we exchanged IG’s & both kind of assumed we’d never hear from each other again. For some reason something told me that this stranger was supposed to be in my life. 
2 weeks later I came back to Edinburgh & we arranged to go for lunch. Everyone always says making friends as an adult is hard but no friendship had ever felt so easy, natural & warm. 
For a year after this lunch I continued visiting Edinburgh monthly as I’d fallen in love with the city & wanted to spend time there to make sure moving was the right choice. Sarah let me stay with her when I flew up (she would even meet me at the airport 🥹) & legit the rest is history 😂
We’ve separately been through some crazy shit in the last 5 years but having Sarah as a friend ensures you never, ever feel alone, you will always feel understood & listened to, & you will ALWAYS end up hysterically laughing. A lil irish angel & sunshine in human form! You da best bitch 🌞✨

JUSTICE FOR BINGO WINGS!
I promise you, NO ONE cares as much as you do. Life is too short to spend it worrying about what parts of your body jiggle or wobble. You & your body deserve to enjoy summer.

When I was a teen I would never have dreamed of spending a day like this, NO chance I would’ve sat in a bikini on a beach. I missed out on so much growing up. Fear truly is the thief of joy. But now at the grand age of 30 I have never felt more content, comfortable & happy in myself. PLEASE say YES to experiences that make you nervous because of your body, you won’t regret it. You deserve to make beautiful memories with friends, family & people that love you regardless of what your body looks like or how you feel about it. You can do it, promise x 

This (not so) secret lil beach is privately owned & it’s never been busy any time I’ve been there! (Granted I’ve never gone on a weekend in august 😅) Just to note, you have to pay £3 to get into the car park so if you go don’t forget your pound coins!!

My favourite hair & makeup looks from the past few weeks! 🎨💁‍♀️ which one is your fave?! ✨

My 6 top products recently:
- @vievemuse skin dew: wear it under /mixed in with foundation or as a highlighter as you get the most beautiful glass skin glow ✨

- @rarebeauty highlighter in ‘mesmerise’: pinky toned highlighter that feels like BUTTER & gives the most insane sheen 🌈 

- @kvdbeauty lock-it foundation: high coverage but never cakey! I use a tiny amount & mix it in the the skin dew! 🤝

- @vievemuse power ink liner: best eyeliner I’ve ever used in my entire 30 years. That is all. 💯 

- @maybelline sky high mascara: fail safe mascara I wear everyday. SO. MUCH. LENGTH. 👁️👄👁️

- @fentybeauty gloss bomb heat in ‘lemon lava’: plumping lip gloss with the most stunning shine & never sticky! 🤌🏼

Oh well HEY 100k friends! 🥹 that’s SO insane right?! Mind-blowing. Never in a million years did I think over 6 years ago when I started uploading pictures of me in outfits, it would grow to be my full time job & my dream job all in one ✨

Plus size fashion & styling, self love & body acceptance is everything to me & I always say I do this for the little Poppy that hated herself, her body, & couldn’t find clothes to fit her. Daaamn if 10 year old me could meet 30 year old me I think she’d think she was the coolest fuckin’ thing EVER. 

Wether you’ve been here for 6 years or for 6 days, thank you for following me, listening to me & supporting me because without you I wouldn’t get to do this - love you all so very very much 🫶

& thank you to @spotlight.management for being the best & most supportive management evaaaaah! 💖

As the weather shifts, so does my skin. My psoriasis *always* flares as it gets colder & the second I get anxious about a flare up, the worse it gets. It’s a never ending cycle 🤷‍♀️
Just uploading these photos I took this morning as a reminder to anyone that struggles with body image, skin issues, auto immune diseases etc. 
You are more than your body, your skin, your marks, your scars. 
I used to cry so much over flare ups like this (especially knowing it’s going to get so much worse than this), and whilst painful & inconvenient, I refuse to let the visual aspect of my skin stop me from living my life & feeling good about myself. 
You still deserve to love yourself, feel sexy, dress in clothes that make you feel amazing & get naked in front of your partner.
If you’re struggling right now, know that you’re not alone & I fuckin’ love you & think you’re beautiful 💖✨

A lil belated 2023 recap 🫶 
I tend to feel low at the start of a new year, reflecting on the 12 months that have gone by, wondering if I’ve achieved enough & feeling overwhelmed at the prospect of a new year. 
Making these recap reels really helps me see the year in a positive way; the amount I’ve laughed, danced terribly, the good food I’ve eaten, the places I’ve visited, and most importantly the beautiful people I’ve shared all those memories with. 

A reminder to myself & anyone else that might need to hear it, the new year doesn’t have to mean a ‘new me, new start’, it can just mean carrying on as usual. You’re doing great, don’t forget it 😊💖
